gomodel:SYNGO_963  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Proenkephalin-A is a precursor that is cleaved into 8 peptides, of which Met-enkephalin is one. Met-enkephalin is a major agonist of the Mu-opioid receptor.\n\nThe paper uses pre-embedding peroxidase immunostaining for electron microscopy to characterize the location of Met5-enkephalin in the rat Nucleus locus coeruleus. The majority of the peroxidase signal is found in presynaptic profiles (examples in figure 2-4). In the presynapse, strong signal was found associated with large-dense core vesicles (examples in figure 2-4). There was also peroxidase signal in the rim of small synaptic vesicles (figure 2 and text) in a subset of labelled terminals. Occasionally plasma membrane immunoreactivity was detected.. Experimental description: Four adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (Taconic Farms, NJ; 200-250 g) were used in this study." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_963" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

